#- §lFade in. §0§lExt,§0
§0§lMount Augustan§0
§0§lStreet.§0
§0
§7§oSiksta is walking alone, §7§odown the dark §7§ostreets. A dark figure §7§oappears in the gloom §7§oof a nearby building.
#- §1PapaPound:§0 Siksta.§0
§0
§7§oSiksta stops walking§0
§0
§1Siksta:§0 §7§o(§f.§7§oinner §7§omonologue§f.§7§o)§0 It was a voice from the past, a voice I had hoped would stay there. §7§oaloud§0 Papa_Pound. What brings you to Mount Augusta this time of night?
#- §1PapaPound:§0 I like the air here. Somewhat... freer.§0
§0
§1Siksta:§0 Cut the crap Papa. What do you want?§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 You know what I want.
#- §1Siksta:§0 I gave that life up. I don't do that anymore.§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 You were the best. You think I could go to Chrischrispie for this? You think I would go to anyone but the best for this job?
#- §1Siksta:§0 I GAVE IT UP. I don't write porn anymore, not after...§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 §7§owhisper§0 Papa_Pounded was a masterpiece§0
§0
§1Siksta:§0 STOP. I don't want to talk about it.
#- §1PapaPound:§0 I'm not asking you to. I'm asking you to write something new. One last book, Siksta. One last chance to make a difference.§0
§0
§1Siksta:§0 One last run at the game...§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 Exactly.
#- §1Siksta:§0 And what's the prize?§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 It's not the prize you should worry about Siksta. It's the cost of failure.§0
§0
§7§oPapa walks out from §7§othe shadows, flicks a §7§ocigarette into the §7§ostreet.
#- §7§oHis breastplate is §7§oblazoned with Noxian §7§oemblems§0
§0
§1PapaPound:§0 The fate of the server hangs in the balance.§0
§0
§1Siksta:§0 Who are the subjects, Papa?
#- §1PapaPound:§0 Sintralin and Shadedjon. Nox and Eden. World Police and HCF. The whole server needs this, Siksta. We need you.§0
§0
§7§oSiksta steps forward, §7§ostanding eye-to-eye §7§owith Papa.
#- §1Siksta:§0 I'll write your damned book.§0
§0
§7§oSiksta turns and §7§ocontinues walking §7§odown the path, Papa §7§oleans back against §7§othe building and lights §7§oanother cigarette.§0
§0
§0§lEnd scene.
